WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'HaffaChainy', that's what this game is: half a Chainy...

...but it's much more than Haff the fun!

  The game is based on 'Chainy', another one of my 'Workbench'
games, the difference is that 'HaffaChainy' is played on an 6 by 8
tile board while 'Chainy' is played on a 12 by 8 tile board.

  The idea of the game is to rotate chainlinks so they form chains
of 3 or more chainlinks of the same colour. The more links there
are in a chain, the more points you get. Once a chain of 3 or more
links is made, it is removed from the board and the links located
in the upper spaces will fall in the emptied spaces.

  To play, click on any chainlink you desire, this will rotate it
by 90 degrees. If a neighbouring link is compatible and of the
same colour, both chainlinks will connect together.

  As you progress in the game, nonmoveable chainlinks (these are
'frozen' in ice cubes), blocks that appear on the lowest rows,
bombs or 'siamese tiles' may appear on the game board.

  A 'Top 10' records the best scores and saves them on disk.

  Have fun!

